;; Modules that do NOT trigger driver tests in CI when changed, even though the dependency graph says
;; `driver`/`transforms` transitively depend on them (see `mage.modules/driver-affecting-overrides`).
;;
;; Every entry is an unverified bet that the coupling is not real enough to break a driver test. The
;; set should only shrink: its size is a module-boundary ratchet (`:driver-test-exempt-modules`), and
;; `metabase.core.modules-test` fails any entry the graph no longer justifies (not a declared module,
;; or no longer upstream of a driver-triggering module).
